DOCUMENT();       

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
#           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
#           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
#           "extraAnswerEvaluators.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
"MathObjects.pl",
"AnswerFormatHelp.pl",
"PGcourse.pl",
           );
       
TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.

Context("Numeric");

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$r = random(3.401,3.421,.001);
$dec = $r/100;
$b = 1-$dec;
$h = round(log(.5)/log($b)*1000)/1000;

BEGIN_TEXT

Find the half-life of an element, which decays at a rate of $r$PERCENT per day.
$BR
$BR
The half-life is \{ ans_rule(10) \} days. (Round to the nearest 0.001 days.)
\{ AnswerFormatHelp("numbers") \}

END_TEXT

ANS( Real("$h")->cmp(tolerance=>0.0006,tolType=>"absolute") );

#ANS( num_cmp($h,tol=>0.0006) );

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR 

Since the decay factor is $b =1 - $dec, the formula for the decay equation, starting with a quantity of $BITALIC a $EITALIC and time $BITALIC t $EITALIC in days, is \( Q = a($b)^t\).
$BR $SPACE $BR
The half-life will be the value of $BITALIC t $EITALIC for which $BITALIC Q $EITALIC is $BITALIC a${EITALIC}/2, or half of the initial quantity $BITALIC a${EITALIC}.  Thus, we solve the equation for $BITALIC Q $EITALIC = $BITALIC a${EITALIC}/2:
$BR $SPACE $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ a/2 = a($b)^t \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ 1/2 = ($b)^t \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \log{(1/2)} = \log{\left( ($b)^t \right)} \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \log{(1/2)} = t \ \log{($b)} \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ t = \frac{\log{(1/2)}}{\log{($b)}} \approx $h \).
$BR $SPACE $BR
So the half-life is about $h days.
$BR
END_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();   # This should be the last executable line in the problem.